'''Esch-sur-Alzette communal council''' ({{lang-fr|Conseil communal de Esch-sur-Alzette}}) is the [[Local government|local council]] for the [[Communes of Luxembourg|commune]] of [[Esch-sur-Alzette]], in south-western [[Luxembourg]].
It consists of nineteen members, elected every six years by [[proportional representation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esch.lu/Default.aspx?id=a6d38fc0-7e4a-43bb-b4ae-d1edf1d1c24e |title=Les Fonctions et Missions du Conseil Communal |accessdate=2007-09-01 |date= |publisher=Ville de Esch-sur-Alzette |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070926221659/http://www.esch.lu/Default.aspx?id=a6d38fc0-7e4a-43bb-b4ae-d1edf1d1c24e |archivedate=2007-09-26 |language=fr |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> The last elections were held on 9 October 2005, and resulted in a victory for the [[Luxembourg Socialist Workers' Party]] (LSAP). In the ''[[Collège échevinal (Luxembourg)|collège échevinal]]'', the LSAP forms a coalition with [[The Greens (Luxembourg)|The Greens]], who have the third-largest contingent, under the leadership of LSAP [[Mayor of Esch-sur-Alzette|mayor]] [[Lydia Mutsch]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esch.lu/Default.aspx?id=b4288b29-e52a-4427-937e-265c363858c8 |title=Le Collège Echevinal 2005-2011 |accessdate=2007-09-01 |date= |publisher=Ville de Esch-sur-Alzette |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070926221602/http://www.esch.lu/Default.aspx?id=b4288b29-e52a-4427-937e-265c363858c8 |archivedate=2007-09-26 |language=fr |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
