{{Infobox government agency |agency_name = Special Security Forces Command |nativename = |nativename_a = قيادة قوة الأمن الخاصة |nativename_r = |logo = |logo_width = 160px |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |picture = |picture_width = |picture_caption = |formed = 1930 |commander = |preceding1 = |preceding2 = <!-- (etc.) --> |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = [[Government of Bahrain]] |headquarters = Diwan Fort, [[Manama]] |region_code = BH |coordinates = {{coord|26|13|22.47|N|50|34|33.8|E|region:BH}} |motto = Special Security Forces, Always Forward! |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = |minister1_pfo = |minister2_name = |minister2_pfo = <!-- (etc.) --> |deputyminister1_name = |deputyminister1_pfo = |deputyminister2_name = |deputyminister2_pfo = <!-- (etc.) --> |chief1_name = Brigadier General [[Abdullah Al-Zayed]] |chief1_position = Commander of Special Security Forces |chief2_name = |chief2_position = <!-- (etc.) --> |agency_type = |parent_department = [[Ministry of Interior (Bahrain)|Ministry of Interior]] |parent_agency = |child1_agency = |child2_agency = <!-- (etc.) --> |keydocument1 = <!-- (etc.) --> |website = http://www.interior.gov.bh/default_en.aspx |footnotes = |map = |map_width = |map_caption = }}
The '''Special Security Force Command''' ({{lang-ar|قيادة قوة الأمن الخاصة}}) is a [[paramilitary]] law enforcement body in [[Bahrain]] under the command of the [[Ministry of the Interior (Bahrain)|Ministry of the Interior]]. The SSFC is more commonly referred to as the "Special Security Forces", the "Special Forces", "Bahrain Special Security Forces (BSSF) or as the "riot police" ({{lang-ar|الشغب}}).
==Accusations== {{see|Human rights in Bahrain}} The Special Security Forces have been accused of [[human rights abuse]]s, in trying to suppress pro-democratic activity in Bahrain. The SSFC has been at the front line of the Bahrain government's crackdown on pro-democracy protesters during the [[Bahraini uprising (2011–present)|Bahraini uprising]] in the [[Arab Spring]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Brutal crackdown on demonstrators in Bahrain|url=http://www.frontlinedefenders.org/node/14480|accessdate=4 September 2011|newspaper=[[Front Line (NGO)]]}}</ref>
In November 2007, Bahrain signed a cooperation agreement with France under which French police officers working in the [[Compagnies Républicaines de Sécurité]] have provided training to Bahrain's SSFC.<ref name=HRW>{{cite news|title=Torture Redux|url=https://www.hrw.org/en/node/88200/section/5|newspaper=[[Human Rights Watch]]|date=8 February 2010|page=5}}</ref> A company of the SSFC were deployed to [[Afghanistan]] to provide base security at the [[United States]]'s [[Camp Leatherneck]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bahrain troops to lead Afghan special forces|url=http://www.gulf-daily-news.com/NewsDetails.aspx?storyid=294605|newspaper=[[Gulf Daily News]]|date=24 December 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=State Department cables detail U.S. links to Bahrain|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2011/02/21/AR2011022104313.html|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]|date=22 February 2011}}</ref>
